The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 24: The RBI has directed banks to provide individuals with their credit information obtained from entities such as Cibil if the customer expresses his desire for the same. The report can be accessed for a maximum fee of Rs 50. Individuals who have taken a loan from a commercial bank will not have to wait till next year to gain access to their credit report.                             
	 Mumbai, June 24: The Bank of India (BoI) plans to raise Rs 13,000 crore through the issuance of securities. The board has approved to raise capital through issuance of innovative perpetual debt instruments, preference shares and bonds.                            
	 New Delhi, June 24: The government will open two integrated textile parks to boost the sector and pump in additional resources of Rs 1,660 crore to support the cotton price and launch training programmes for 50,000 weavers.                            
	 New Delhi, June 24: Cals Refineries, a Spice Energy Group company, will tie up funds for its proposed $1.1-billion (Rs 5,400 crore) refinery project at Haldia by the end of July, CEO Manabendra Guha Roy said.                             
	 Calcutta, June 24: KEC International, an RPG group company, has bagged three orders worth Rs 110 crore. One project is in Peru and the other two are in Chhattisgarh.                                                                                                                           
